[Event "Kasparov's Immortal"]
[Site "Wijk aan Zee"]
[Date "1999.01.20"]
[White "Garry Kasparov"]
[Black "Veselin Topalov"]
[Result "1-0"]

{One of the greatest games ever played. Kasparov unleashes a king hunt spanning nearly the entire board.} 1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 Bg7 5. Qd2 c6 6. f3 b5 7. Nge2 Nbd7 8. Bh6 {Exchanging Black's powerful fianchettoed bishop.} Bxh6 9. Qxh6 Bb7 10. a3 e5 11. O-O-O Qe7 12. Kb1 a6 13. Nc1 {Rerouting the knight to d3 — a deep regrouping.} O-O-O 14. Nb3 exd4 15. Rxd4 c5 16. Rd1 Nb6 17. g3 Kb8 18. Na5 Ba8 19. Bh3 d5 20. Qf4+ Ka7 21. Rhe1 d4 22. Nd5! {The first sacrifice. White gives up a knight to rip open the position.} Nbxd5 23. exd5 Qd6 (23... Nxd5 24. Qxf7 {Winning.}) 24. Rxd4!! {A stunning rook sacrifice! The point is to open lines against the exposed king.} cxd4 (24... Qxd4 25. Re7+ Kb8 (25... Kb6 26. Qxd4+ Kxa5 27. b4+ {With a devastating attack.}) 26. Qxd4 cxd4 27. Nc6+ {Winning.}) 25. Re7+! Kb6 (25... Qxe7 26. Qxd4+ Kb8 27. Qb6+ {Leads to mate.}) 26. Qxd4+ Kxa5 27. b4+! Ka4 (27... Kxb4 28. Qb6+ {And Black's king is hunted down.}) 28. Qc3! {Threatening Qb3 mate. The king is trapped deep in enemy territory.} Qxd5 29. Ra7! Bb7 (29... Qd1+ 30. Kb2 Qd4 31. Qxd4 Rd5 (31... Rxd4 32. Rxa8 {Winning.}) 32. Qxd5 Nxd5 33. Rxa8 {White is winning.}) 30. Rxb7 Qc4 {Trying to trade queens.} 31. Qxf6 Kxa3 (31... Rd1+ 32. Kb2 Qd4+ 33. Qxd4 Rxd4 34. Rxf7 {White wins.}) 32. Qxa6+ Kxb4 33. c3+! Kxc3 34. Qa1+ Kd2 35. Qb2+ Kd1 36. Bf1! {A quiet move amidst the chaos — the bishop joins the final mating net.} Rd2 (36... Qxf1 37. Qc2#) 37. Rd7! Rxd7 38. Bxc4 bxc4 39. Qxh8 Rd3 40. Qa8 {White is completely winning with queen against rook.} c3 41. Qa4+ Ke1 42. f4 f5 43. Kc1 Rd2 44. Qa7 {Kasparov's immortal game — a king hunt across the entire board.} 1-0
